      <hedline>
        <hl1>Two Cheers For Sweatshops</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Two cheers for sweatshops? With a third cheer for what? Naked corporate greed (Nicholas D. Kristof and Sheryl WuDunn, Sept. 24)? Surely, huge corporations like Nike can devote a tiny part of their earnings to ensure that their workers are paid a living wage, work under humane conditions and aren't forced into 100-hour workweeks.</p>
        <p>Claire Tuck  Albany</p>
      </block>
